1
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:09,000
Klara's coming here next week.
Klara下个星期要到这里来.

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:10,300
Do we need a plan?
我们要计划一下吗?

3
00:00:11,300 --> 00:00:13,200
What kind of plan?
什么计划?

4
00:00:14,200 --> 00:00:16,600
How should we impress her?
我们应该怎样给她留下好印象?

5
00:00:16,700 --> 00:00:19,100
We will impress her with our fine work.
我们要用我们出色的工作来给她留下深刻的印象.

6
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:25,400
Nancy, I used to say that when I worked with your husband and all the other lawyers in state government.
Nancy, 以前我与你丈夫以及州政府的其他律师共事时经常这么说.

7
00:00:25,450 --> 00:00:28,300
But now, we are in the design business.
但现在, 我们经营的是设计行业.

8
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:33,700
It could use a facelift.
这房间可以整理一下.

9
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:52,700
Look what I found. Wow!
看我发现了什么. Wow!

10
00:00:52,750 --> 00:00:56,100
I covered the chairs and moved the sofa in here.
我给椅子加了套子, 把沙发移了进来.

11
00:00:56,200 --> 00:01:00,100
I picked up a new album for presenting our work.
我买了个新的影集来展现我们的作品.

12
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:01,400
Perfect. 
太棒了.

13
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:35,300
Hello. You bought a what?
喂. 你买了什么?

14
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:48,800
We needed something here anyway.
反正我们这里还需要点东西.

15
00:01:57,500 --> 00:02:03,117
I called Klara, confirmed the time, gave her directions and mailed her a map.
我给Klara打了电话, 确定了时间, 告诉她怎么走, 还给她寄了张地图.

16
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:07,900
Is there anything else we can do?
我们还能做点别的什么吗?

17
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:12,800
This is all very charming.
这一切太迷人了.

18
00:02:15,300 --> 00:02:17,400
Who could that be?
可能是谁呢?

19
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:19,496
I'll get it. Excuse me.
我去开门. 失陪一会儿.

20
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:23,053
More tea, Klara?
再来点儿茶, Klara?

21
00:02:23,150 --> 00:02:24,300
Yes. Thank you. 
好的. 谢谢.

22
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:28,750
You know it's not easy being gracious these days.
你知道这年头做到殷勤有礼可不容易.

23
00:02:28,850 --> 00:02:31,000
No, no, it isn't.
可不是嘛.

24
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:34,300
Aren't they gorgeous?
漂亮吗?

25
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:35,200
Who sent them?
是谁送的?

26
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:36,447
Let's see. 
让我们看看.

27
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:41,800
"Thank you for making my home so beautiful.
"谢谢你们把我的房子装修得如此漂亮.

28
00:02:41,850 --> 00:02:43,800
Best wishes, Janet Wu."
祝一切顺利, Janet Wu."

29
00:02:43,860 --> 00:02:45,750
Janet Wu?
Janet Wu?

30
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:50,300
Just one of our many satisfied customers.
只是对我们的服务满意的许多顾客中的一位.

31
00:02:54,700 --> 00:02:56,300
You were saying, Klara?
你刚才说什么来着, Klara?

